cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a new approach to Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for image synthesis, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new player in GANs, called reconstructor, which utilizes an auto-encoding scheme, indicating the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents experiments with image synthesis, which could also fall under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
